The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, March 3: Balmer Lawrie amp; Company today said its UK-based subsidiary Balmer Lawrie (UK) Ltd had launched a joint venture firm in Indonesia. The company established the 50:50 joint venture in collaboration with Indonesian Company PT Imani Wicaksana. The joint venture firm  PT Imani Ganda Utama  would manufacture and market greases and lubricants in Indonesia.                            
	 Mumbai, March 3: UK-based financial services company Prudential plc, which has a life insurance tie-up with ICICI, today said its relationship with the Indian financial services major remains strong. Prudential plc has entered into a $35.5-billion deal to buy American International Groups life insurance business in Asia.                            
	 New Delhi, March 3: The government will extend Rs 500 crore capital infusion into state-owned India Infrastructure Finance Company Ltd (IIFCL) in 2010-11. The budget provision is for equity support to meet the capital requirement of the company during the year.                            
	 New Delhi, March 3: The countrys mutual fund industry witnessed a near three per cent jump in the average assets under management in February to Rs 7.81 lakh crore.                            
	 New Delhi, March 3: Indian Oil Corp is looking at equity partners for its Rs 29,777-crore Paradip refinery project in Orissa.
                                                                                                                          
